r6103 | mcgrathr@chromium.org | Mon Jul 18 12:48:23 PDT 2011

Changed paths:
 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/SConstruct?r1=6103&amp;r2=6102&amp;pathrev=6103

Add --mode=nacl_irt_test

This adds a new scons mode that builds most of the non-browser tests in an
additional variant environment where they are linked for and run with the
IRT.  To build correctly, the nacl_env must be built too.  So one can use
e.g. ./scons --mode=opt-host,nacl,nacl_irt_test irt_tests to build and run
all the IRT variants of tests that normally run without IRT.

The intent is to make nacl_irt_test automagically implied by nacl,
as we do with nacl_irt.  We're not doing this yet because a handful
of the tests are not yet working and still being investigated.

